"{\"uid\": \"abc.net.au-listen-programs-am-record-falls-in-olympic-swimming-trials-103971952\", \"text\": \"Program:AM  Presented by  Golden Girl Ariarne Titmus has broken the 200m freestyle world record at the Australian Olympic trials in Brisbane.  She's heading to Paris, alongside former record holder Molly O'Callaghan.  Some swimmers have qualified for their fourth Games, while others are about to make their Olympic debut.  ((AP: Charlie Riedel))  Published:ThuThu 4 Dec 2025 at 8:10pm  Published:WedWed 3 Dec 2025 at 8:10pm  Published:TueTue 2 Dec 2025 at 8:10pm  Published:MonMon 1 Dec 2025 at 8:10pm  Download the ABC listen app to hear more of your favourite podcasts  We acknowledge Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as the     First Australians and Traditional Custodians of the lands where we     live, learn and work.\"}"